---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../lib/site';

const aboutDescription = `About ${SITE_TITLE} — a novel for readers aged twelve and up.`;
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={aboutDescription}>
  <SiteHeader slot="header" />

  <div class="container prose">
    <h1 class="page-title">About this book</h1>

    <blockquote>
      <p>
        <em>"Some treasures are buried beneath the earth.</em>
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>Others are found in the friends who choose to search for them."</em>
      </p>
    </blockquote>

    <p>
      This is the story of four young heroes who became caught up in the mystery of an
      ancient civilisation known only as <strong>Ethium</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>
      The events in this book are based on our Dungeons &amp; Dragons campaign. Every
      battle was fought, every difficult decision was made, and every ridiculous idea
      really happened around our gaming table.
    </p>

    <p>
      Some conversations have been expanded and descriptions added so that the adventure
      reads like a fantasy novel, but the story remains faithful to the adventures of
      our heroes.
    </p>

    <p>
      This manuscript is a living document. As the adventure continues, new chapters
      will be added and earlier chapters refined, until the campaign is complete.
    </p>

    <h2>Dramatis Personae</h2>

    <h3>The Heroes</h3>

    <h4>Thorn Axehand</h4>
    <p>
      A brave young half-orc fighter who rarely hesitates when danger appears. Armed
      with his trusty axe and an even stronger sense of loyalty, Thorn often finds
      himself leading the group into adventure.
    </p>

    <h4>Loki</h4>
    <p>
      Thorn's faithful guard dog. Fearless, loyal and blessed with an excellent nose,
      Loki has an uncanny habit of finding trouble — and occasionally saving the day.
    </p>

    <h4>Derek</h4>
    <p>
      A dependable dwarven cleric named after one of the greatest heroes from
      <em>Stranger Things</em>. Calm under pressure and always ready to protect his
      friends, Derek is the heart of the group.
    </p>

    <h4>Dave</h4>
    <p>
      A very young copper dragonborn wizard whose favourite spell launches magically
      propelled potatoes instead of glowing bolts of force. Despite his unusual style,
      his magic has saved the party more than once. When truly threatened, he can
      unleash the poisonous breath of his dragon ancestors.
    </p>

    <h4>Nibbles McPicklepants</h4>
    <p>
      A dragonborn rogue with quick hands, sharp eyes and an endless curiosity.
      Nibbles is always searching for hidden treasure, secret passages or his next
      upgrade. One day he hopes to own enough poison to coat every blade he carries.
    </p>

    <h3>Friends</h3>

    <h4>Mara</h4>
    <p>A courier rescued from goblins while carrying a mysterious map to Fallcrest.</p>

    <h4>Sergeant Murgaddin</h4>
    <p>
      A veteran member of the Fallcrest town guard who quickly recognises that the
      companions are more than ordinary travellers.
    </p>

    <h4>Tobbs</h4>
    <p>The cheerful halfling apprentice of the legendary wizard Nimozaran.</p>

    <h4>Nimozaran</h4>
    <p>
      The greatest wizard in Fallcrest. He has not been seen outside his tower for
      many years.
    </p>

    <h3>Enemies</h3>

    <h4>The Hammers</h4>
    <p>A violent street gang operating around Fallcrest.</p>

    <h4>The Gang of Four</h4>
    <p>A powerful criminal organisation based in Sunfall, the capital of Almenor.</p>

    <p>
      Start from the <a href="/chapters/">table of contents</a>, or jump straight in
      with <a href="/">Begin reading</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose h2,
  .prose h3,
  .prose h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-edge);
    padding-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .prose h3 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin: 1.75rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .prose h4 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.35rem;
  }
</style>
